						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is badly damaged in the first ten lines. It records a gift of 12(1/2) <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tirumālpēṟuḍaiya-Mahādēva by Kaṇṇandai Kuṭṭattāḻi of Vaḍagarai in Śembūr-kōṭṭam, who is said to have deposited the amount with the <hi rend="italic">Ūrār</hi> of Nelvāyil in Valla-nāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
